      - 'Nevertheless, the church was very pleased, and your devotion brought even
        more people to the clergy. '
      - 'Some nobles also thought the burning as a fun spectacle. '
      - 'As for <PlayerLose>, his lack of action will be remembered by the alchemists
        and merchants, for letting the kingdom lose its freedom. '
      - "The commoners also speak of him as weak and indecisive.\r"
  - identifier: 2
